cs.CV, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper deals with integral images, which are widely used in computer vision algorithms for feature detection and object recognition. 
2. cs.EM (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper discusses efficient algorithms for computation and storage of integral images in resource-constrained embedded vision systems, which is an emerging technology area. 
3. cs.AR (Augmented Reality) is another possible category as integral images are used in AR applications for real-time tracking and recognition of objects. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes hardware algorithms for efficient computation of integral images, which can be applied in embedded vision systems for control and automation. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category as the paper discusses parallel algorithms for computation of integral images, which can be applied in distributed and parallel computing systems.
